Mom and I stopped in for a quick lunch on my February trip to Arizona.
We were in between errands for my Grandmother and needed a place to gather our bearings and have something to eat.
We split a sandwich with chicken, avocado, lettuce, tomato and mustard on a dark rye (something Panera doesn't have) and it was tasty.
