Paradise Bakery has good food for reasonable prices, and I eat here fairly often.
I particularly enjoy their salads.
I don't think I've ever paid more than $10 for a lunch, which is about what I'd expect at a place like this.
It does seem like their menus have decreased lately, though.
They used to have this delicious steak salad, but it is now gone, and one of the employees told me their southwest chicken caesar (also one of my favorites) is on the way out, too.
Apparently Panera bought out the chain about five years ago and has been making gradual changes to the menu, which as far as I am concerned are definitely for the worse.
I'll keep eating here for now, but if the menu loses too many more items which I enjoy I enjoy I may stop coming.

